HEADWORD: Blindly
<hw>Blind"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Without sight, discernment, or
understanding; without thought, investigation, knowledge, or purpose of
one's own.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By his imperious mistress <qex>blindly</qex> led.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blind man's buff</ent>⟦br⟧
